/wave Bjond<br>
<br>
I chose my character's first name because it was short, quick and easy to spell. I had no intention of choosing a long surname either, I figured if I ever actually made it to my 20th season with a character, I would choose a short surname too. This is my first real character on EQ so getting a surname is kinda fun for me. A rite of passage so to speak since I've never had a character in the 20's before. <br>
<br>
Having said that, my guild's name is a bit long, so the banner started growing, not really any control over that. For roleplay reasons, I'm getting a surname in a few weeks that I didn't choose outright but had a big hand in the decision making process for it, obviously. And it's long. So my original intention of having a short name has turned into having a banner that will in all probability be longer than my half elf is tall.   <br>
<br>
/shrug what can ya do?<br>
